{
  "name": "ultracode-dynamic-workflow-codex",
  "version": "3.5.0",
  "created_at_utc": "2026-06-14T16:06:38.144083+00:00",
  "skill_name": "ultracode",
  "activation": "$ultracode only",
  "notes": "PACKAGE_MANIFEST.json excludes itself from the file hash list.",
  "primary_changes": [
    "Run artifacts now default to <project>/.ultracode/runs/<id> (writable) instead of <project>/.codex/ultracode/runs/<id> — Codex's workspace-write sandbox makes .codex read-only (verified: .codex EROFS while project root and other dotdirs are writable).",
    "Run dir created chmod 0700 and <project>/.ultracode/.gitignore '*' written, so artifacts (which can hold private/business data) are owner-only and never committed; fixes the world-readable-/tmp leak on shared hosts.",
    "uc_route/uc_bootstrap write <project>/.ultracode/last_run_dir; uc_hook_router._latest_run_dir and uc_adversarial_verify auto-discovery read the pointer first (then .ultracode/runs, then legacy .codex/ultracode/runs), so the Stop gate tracks the run even when --out-dir redirects it.",
    "stop_nudges.json and project state.json moved off read-only .codex to .ultracode (otherwise the Stop escape-valve counter write fails silently -> infinite block).",
    "Route heuristic no longer mislabels read-only audits as implementation: added 审查/审计/评审/assess to audit keywords and demoted hypothetical 'already implemented' cues.",
    "uc_verify --read-only skips irrelevant test/lint/build gates for audit tasks; adversarial gate no longer flags 'detected-not-executed' for read-only runs. Reviewer lane tightened to avoid full src/ re-sweep. Sharpened run-dir-not-writable hint."
  ],
